{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"26bee7cf-9acd-48aa-9d07-b8ec4594d9f2","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"601003a0-cadb-4fd5-8bf3-e23946f8a8cd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about dotnet CLI usage - I can answer directly without needing to explore files.","outputTokens":166,"requestId":"E3D1:321F09:5AC722:686AF5:6A0524A1"},"id":"dd890f11-1df6-4d07-8bfc-561e9aad811d","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:25:59.055Z","parentId":"765bb8dc-d3c8-40b8-9df1-895783ed4478"}
